        "content": "<p>I’m using the following test function to prove a first-order stochastic theory. Special thanks to Yury G. Kudryashov and Junyan Xu for their kind assistance!</p>\n<p>noncomputable def v_test (x₀ δ : ℝ) : ℝ → ℝ := fun x =&gt;<br>\n  if |x - x₀| ≤ δ then x else if x &lt; x₀-δ then x₀-δ else x₀+δ </p>\n<p>lemma v_test_continuous (x₀ δ : ℝ) (hδ : δ &gt; 0) : Continuous (v_test x₀ δ) :=by</p>",
        "id": 511544278,
        "sender_full_name": "lijingyuan",
        "timestamp": 1744337041
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Please read <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/wiki/Code-in-backticks\">#backticks</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mwe.html\">#mwe</a></p>",
