    {
        "content": "<p>There are relevant lemmas around <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Piecewise.html#continuous_if\">continuous_if</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Order/OrderClosed.html#continuous_if_le\">continuous_if_le</a>, but in this case you can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/ProjIcc.html#Set.projIcc\">Set.projIcc</a> (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Order/ProjIcc.html#continuous_projIcc\">continuous_projIcc</a> is marked <code>@[continuity]</code> so you can use the <code>continuity</code> tactic to prove continuity. (There's also <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Order/OrderClosed.html#continuous_max\">continuous_max</a> but it's not marked <code>@[continuity]</code>.)</p>",
        "id": 511616168,
        "sender_full_name": "Junyan Xu",
        "timestamp": 1744367475
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"224323\">Junyan Xu</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/113489-new-members/topic/How.20to.20prove.20a.20.20piecewise.20linear.20function.20is.20continuous.20.3F/near/511616168\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>There are relevant lemmas around <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Piecewise.html#continuous_if\">continuous_if</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Order/OrderClosed.html#continuous_if_le\">continuous_if_le</a>, but in this case you can use <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Order/Interval/Set/ProjIcc.html#Set.projIcc\">Set.projIcc</a> (<a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Order/ProjIcc.html#continuous_projIcc\">continuous_projIcc</a> is marked <code>@[continuity]</code> so you can use the <code>continuity</code> tactic to prove continuity. (There's also <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/Topology/Order/OrderClosed.html#continuous_max\">continuous_max</a> but it's not marked <code>@[continuity]</code>.)</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It works!  Thank you!</p>",
